article.headline: Fordham 91, St. Bonaventure 60
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. (AP) -- Bryant Dunston scored 25 points and recorded 11 rebounds to lead Fordham in a 91-60 win over St. Bonaventure Wednesday. Kevin Anderson scored 16 points with an 88 percent shooting average for Fordham (16-11, 9-6 Atlantic 10). Sebastian Greene added 14 points and Marcus Stout contributed 11. Fordham jumped out to a quick 8-2 lead a minute and a half into the game and never trailed. In the first, the Rams built a lead as large as 18, shot 60 percent from the field and held a 45-29 halftime lead. In the second half, the Rams outscored St. Bonaventure, 46-31, on their way to a season-high 91 points -- 28 above their season average. A.J. Hawkins led St. Bonaventure (7-21, 4-11 A-10) offensively for the sixth time in the last seven games with 17 points. Tyler Relph hit three 3-pointers on his way to 14 points and Michael Lee added 13.
